rComments: Prof Liliane Dionne is a dedicated and organized professor. She invests time in her students and is interested in both education and research. Prof Dionne has high expectations and students need to work hard in her class. Prof Dionne is always willing to help students both in and out of class. She is well-respected by her colleagues and students.

Avoid this professor at all cost. Heavy lectures that are completely useless for your knowledge and lots of waste of time. If you're interested in acquiring real competencies in qualitative research, this is not the course for you. Don't expect to get a good grade, she always has something negative to say if you don't share the same interests.
